io.confluent.ksql.test.parser

Class SqlTestReader

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.confluent.ksql.test.parser.SqlTestReader
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Iterator<TestStatement>

    public final class SqlTestReader
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Iterator<TestStatement>
    The SqlTestReader is an iterator over a test case that will return one test statement to execute at a time.

    Since some test directives are not part of the ksqlDB grammar and are handled via non-default ANTLR channels, this parser has a more complex iteration. Specifically, the reader uses the SqlBaseParser to read statements, but checks to see if any directives were skipped in the underlying hidden channels.
